# Eval case: ai-budget-coach

IDEA="Build a local-first AI budgeting coach for one user. Ingest bank and credit-card CSVs, auto-categorize transactions with a deterministic rules engine, compute monthly budgets versus actuals, and use a local LLM to narrate plain-English coaching tips from structured summaries only — never raw transactions. Output a monthly Markdown coaching report with overspend alerts and savings nudges."

CONTEXT="Target: single user, laptop-only, no cloud sync. Stack: Python CLI; Pandas; DuckDB (encrypted local DB); Ollama 7B-8B optional; Jinja2 for report templates. Formats: 3 CSV templates (bank, credit card, wallet); manual entry otherwise. Limits: max 12 budget categories; 1 user profile. Non-goals: React UI; cloud LLM default; auto-payments; investment advice; tax filing; multi-user; PDF/charts; sending transactions to any LLM. Defer: goal tracking; scenario what-if; mobile app."
